.TH FLATPAK-AUTOMATIC 1
.SH NAME
flatpak-automatic \- Automated, templated Flatpak updates
.SH ARCHITECTURE
The daemon operates in two parallel modes: System (Root) and User (Rootless).
.SH SYSTEM DEPLOYMENT
To manage system-wide installations:
.PP
\fBsudo systemctl enable flatpak-automatic.timer\fR
.br
\fBsudo systemctl start flatpak-automatic.timer\fR
.SH USER DEPLOYMENT
To manage user-specific installations securely without root:
.PP
\fBsystemctl --user enable flatpak-automatic-user.timer\fR
.br
\fBsystemctl --user start flatpak-automatic-user.timer\fR
.SH NOTIFICATIONS
Outputs are managed via templates in config/templates/, supporting Desktop, HTML/Markdown Mail, and Minimal text logs.
